    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>PageRank</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            margin: 20px;\n        }\n        .container {\n            max-width: 600px;\n            margin: 40px auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n        .row {\n            display: flex;\n            justify-content: space-between;\n        }\n        .col-md-4, .col-md-8 {\n            margin: 10px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-md-4\">\n                <h2>PageRank Algorithm</h2>\n                <p>PageRank is a link analysis algorithm developed by Larry Page and Sergey Brin at Stanford University in 1996.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"col-md-8\">\n                <h2>How it works</h2>\n                <p>PageRank is calculated using a combination of three factors: the number of outgoing links from each page, the link weight (or PageRank score), and the number of links on the page.</p>\n                <p>Here's a step-by-step explanation:</p>\n                <ol>\n                    <li>Start with a single page (P0) with a PageRank score of 1.</li>\n                    <li>For each page (i, 1 ≤ i ≤ N), calculate the PageRank score of each link (j) pointing to page (i) as follows:</li>\n                    <li>PageRank(i, j) = (1/N) \\* (1 - PageRank(j, i)) + (N - 1) \\* PageRank(j, i)</li>\n                    <li>PageRank(i, i) = 1</li>\n                    <li>PageRank(i, j) = PageRank(j, i) \\* LinkWeight(j, i)</li>\n                </ol>\n                <p>Repeat this process until convergence.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        let N = 10; // Number of pages\n        let PageRank = new Array(N).fill(0); // PageRank scores\n        let links = new Array(N).fill(0).map(() => new Array()); // Links\n        let weights = new Array(N).fill(0); // Link weights\n\n        function calculatePageRank() {\n            for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {\n                let sum = 0;\n                for (let j = 0; j < N; j++) {\n                    if (i !== j) {\n                        sum += PageRank[j] * links[i][j];\n                    }\n                }\n                PageRank[i] = 1 / N + (N - 1) / N * sum;\n            }\n        }\n\n        function calculateLinkWeights() {\n            for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {\n                for (let j = 0; j < N; j++) {\n                    if (i !== j) {\n                        links[i][j] = Math.random();\n                        weights[i][j] = links[i][j];\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        let i = 0;\n        let j = 0;\n        calculatePageRank();\n        while (true) {\n            calculateLinkWeights();\n            let newPageRank = new Array(N).fill(0);\n            for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {\n                let sum = 0;\n                for (let j = 0; j < N; j++) {\n                    if (i !== j) {\n                        sum += newPageRank[j] * weights[i][j];\n                    }\n                }\n                newPageRank[i] = 1 / N + (N - 1) / N * sum;\n            }\n            if (newPageRank.every((value, index) => value === PageRank[i])) {\n                break;\n            }\n            PageRank = newPageRank;\n            i = j;\n            j = Math.floor(Math.random() * N);\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
